	Working  with text Files and Directories

Directories:

Que. How to create directory  ?
	mkdir  <foldername>
# mkdir demo

Que. How to make multiple folder 
	mkdir <folder1> <folder2>
     #mkdir  images    files

Que. How to make  sub directories within main directory
	mkdir -p <foldername>/dir1/dir2/dir3
# mkdir -p earth/asia/india/maharashtra/pune

Que. How to create multiple directories at once
	mkdir <mydir>{1..20}    
# mkdir harrypotter{1..7} ->it will create 7 dir with the name of   
                                                         Harrypotter 1 to 7

Que. How to make directories inside another directory
	mkdir <foldername>/{dir1,dir2}

Files:
To create files in linux use
1)	Touch
2)	Cat
3)	Echo
4)	Vi/vim

Que.how to make empty file ?
	touch <filename>
# touch new.txt

Que. How to create  file using cat command ?
	cat > hello.txt
->Hello world!    
*enter
*press cntl + d to save the file

Que.How to append [edit] the content in the same file using cat ?
	cat  >> hello.txt


Que. How to view content in the file ?
	cat filename

Que. How to create file using echo command ?
	echo  “ hello world ”  > file1.txt

Remove/Delete  files or directories :

Que. How to  remove only empty directory ?
	rmdir <foldername>
      # rmdir demo

Que. How to remove directory with content?
	rm -rvf <filename/foldername>

r ->recursive[delete folder/file within file/folder]
v ->view/verbose[shows the  action taken on screen]
f ->forcefully remove

# rm -rvf  earth
Que. How to remove multiple directories with same prefix?
	rm  -rvf   harrypotter{1..7}


